.TH "do_drive_get_GTF" 9 "do_drive_get_GTF" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_drive_get_GTF \- get the drive bootup default taskfile settings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" do_drive_get_GTF
.BI "(ide_drive_t *drive "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *gtf_length "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *gtf_address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *obj_loc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drive" 12
the drive for which the taskfile settings should be retrieved
.IP "gtf_length" 12
number of bytes of _GTF data returned at \fIgtf_address\fP
.IP "gtf_address" 12
buffer containing _GTF taskfile arrays
.IP "obj_loc" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The _GTF method has no input parameters.
It returns a variable number of register set values (registers
hex 1F1..1F7, taskfiles).
The <variable number> is not known in advance, so have ACPI-CA
allocate the buffer as needed and return it, then free it later.

The returned \fIgtf_length\fP and \fIgtf_address\fP are only valid if the
function return value is 0.
